<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The pointer timecb is declared as a non-const pointer (OS_timecb_internal_record_t *timecb) but in OS_TimerGetInfo it is only used for read-only access (timecb->timebase_token and timecb->interval_time). Therefore it could and should be declared as a pointer to const (const OS_timecb_internal_record_t *timecb). This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>
